Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.45,0:00:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I told you there was something
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.09,0:00:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can do right now that would have
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.93,0:00:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,an immediate positive benefit for your brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.19,0:00:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,including your mood and your focus?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.43,0:00:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And what if I told you that same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.49,0:00:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,could actually last a long time and protect
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.41,0:00:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,your brain from different conditions like depression, Alzheimer's disease or dementia?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.51,0:00:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.19,0:00:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am talking about the powerful effects
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.11,0:00:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of physical activity that is simply moving your body
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.95,0:00:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Has immediate, long lasting and protective benefits
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.39,0:00:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,For your brain and that can last for the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.39,0:00:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So what I want to do today is tell you a story
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.49,0:01:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,About how I use my deep understanding of neuroscience
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.93,0:01:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As a professor to essentially do an experiment on myself
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.53,0:01:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In which I discovered the science underlying why exercise
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.87,0:01:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the most transformative thing that you can do for your brain today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.53,0:01:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as a neuroscientist, I know that our brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.33,0:01:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the thing in our head right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.41,0:01:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the most complex structure known to humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.41,0:01:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's one thing to talk about the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.93,0:01:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's another to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.03,0:01:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So here is a real preserved human brain
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.69,0:01:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's going to illustrate two key areas
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.41,0:01:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're going to talk about today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.75,0:01:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is the prefrontal cortex right behind your forehead
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.69,0:01:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,critical for things like decision making, focus, attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.81,0:01:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and your personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.61,0:01:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The second key area is located in the temporal lobe shown right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.87,0:01:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have two temporal lobes on your brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.59,0:01:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The right and the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.85,0:01:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And deep in the temporal lobe is a key structure
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.39,0:02:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,critical for your ability to form and retain
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.89,0:02:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,new long-term memories for facts and events.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.83,0:02:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And that structure is called the hippocampus.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.91,0:02:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've always been fascinated with the hippocampus.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.59,0:02:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,How could it be that an event that lasts just a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.65,0:02:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, your first kiss or the moment your first child was born
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.81,0:02:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,can form a memory that has changed your brain
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.15,0:02:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that lasts an entire lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.75,0:02:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I want to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.93,0:02:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to start and record the activity
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.03,0:02:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of individual brain cells in the hippocampus
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.37,0:02:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as subjects were forming new memories
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and essentially trying to decode how those brief bursts
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.59,0:02:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of electrical activity, which is how neurons communicate with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.07,0:02:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How those brief bursts either allowed us to form
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.67,0:02:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a new memory or did not.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.11,0:02:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But a few years ago I did something very unusual in science.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.41,0:02:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As a full professor of neural science,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.73,0:03:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided to completely switch my research program
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.33,0:03:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because I encountered something that was so amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.99,0:03:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with the potential to change so many lives
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.17,0:03:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that I had to study it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.79,0:03:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I discovered and I experienced the brain-changing effects of exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.53,0:03:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did it in a completely inadvertent way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.71,0:03:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I was actually at the height of all the memory work that I was doing. Data was pouring in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.17,0:03:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was becoming known in my field for all of this memory work
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.77,0:03:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and it should have been going great.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.59,0:03:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It was scientifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.95,0:03:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I stuck my head out of my lab door, I noticed something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.05,0:03:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no social life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.65,0:03:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I spent too much time listening to those brain cells in a dark room by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.43,0:03:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't move my body at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.69,0:04:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I gained 25 pounds and actually took me many years to realize it was actually by myself because I hadn't socialized.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.21,0:04:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I came back thinking, oh my god, I was the weakest person on that trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.79,0:04:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I came back with a mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I never going to feel like the weakest person on a revolving trip again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.41,0:04:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what made me go to the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.55,0:04:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I focused my type A personality on going to all the exercise classes at the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.03,0:04:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.13,0:04:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I went too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.07,0:04:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I noticed is that after every sweat-inducing workout that I tried,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.21,0:04:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I had this great mood boost and this great energy boost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.01,0:04:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what kept me going back to the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.75,0:04:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I started feeling stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.41,0:04:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I started feeling better. I even lost those 25 pounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.07,0:04:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And now fast forward, a year and a half into this regular exercise program.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.89,0:05:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And I noticed something that really made me sit up and take notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.31,0:05:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sitting at my desk writing a research grant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.43,0:05:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And a thought went through my mind that had never gone through my mind before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.93,0:05:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And that thought was, grant writing is going well today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.41,0:05:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the scientists always laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.19,0:05:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say that because grant writing never goes well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.09,0:05:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It is so hard. You're always pulling your hair out trying to come up with that million-dollar winning idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.31,0:05:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But I realized that the grant writing was going well
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.35,0:05:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was able to focus and maintain my attention for longer than I had before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.41,0:05:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And my long-term memory would always seem to be better in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.65,0:05:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's when I put it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.95,0:05:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe all that exercise that I had included and added to my life was changing my brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.07,0:05:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I didn't experiment on myself without even knowing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.51,0:05:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So as a curious neuroscientist, I went to the literature
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.91,0:06:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to see what I could find about what we knew about the effects of exercise on the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.61,0:06:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And what I found was an exciting and growing literature
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.57,0:06:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that was essentially showing everything that I noticed in myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.13,0:06:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Better mood, better energy, better memory, better attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.75,0:06:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the more I learned, the more I realized how powerful exercise was,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.33,0:06:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,which eventually led me to the big decision to completely shift my research focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.47,0:06:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And so now, after several years of really focusing on this question,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.33,0:06:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come to the following conclusion that exercise is the most transformative thing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.55,0:06:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That you can do for your brain today for the following three reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.19,0:06:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Number one, it has immediate effects on your brain. A single workout that you do
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.71,0:06:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,will immediately increase levels of neurotransmitters like dopamine, serotonin, and noradrenaline.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.19,0:07:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That is going to increase your mood right after that workout.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.43,0:07:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly what I was feeling. My lab showed that a single workout
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.25,0:07:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,can improve your ability to shift and focus attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.19,0:07:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And that focus improvement will last for at least two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.15,0:07:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, studies have shown that a single workout
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.59,0:07:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,will improve your reaction times, which basically means that you are going to be faster
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.69,0:07:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,at catching that cup of Starbucks that falls off the counter, which is very, very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.05,0:07:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But these immediate effects are transient. They help you right after.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.87,0:07:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What you have to do is do what I did, that is change your exercise range to regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.91,0:07:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Increase your cardiovascular function to get the long lasting effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.19,0:07:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And these effects are long lasting because exercise actually changes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.01,0:07:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the brain's anatomy, physiology, and function.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.65,0:07:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start with my favorite brain area, the hippocampus.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.59,0:07:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The hippocampus or exercise actually produces brand new brain cells,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.49,0:08:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,new brain cells in the hippocampus, that actually increase its volume
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.65,0:08:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as improve your long-term memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.63,0:08:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And that includes a new and me. Number two, the most common finding in neuroscience studies,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.16,0:08:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at the effects of exercise, long-term exercise is improved attention function.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.24,0:08:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on your prefrontal cortex. You not only get better focus and attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.68,0:08:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but the volume of the hippocampus increases as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.50,0:08:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, you not only get immediate effects on mood with exercise,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.26,0:08:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but those last for a long time, so you get long-lasting increases
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.30,0:08:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in those good mood neurotransmitters. But really, the most transformative thing that exercise
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.44,0:08:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,will do is its protective effects on your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.86,0:08:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you can think about the brain like a muscle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.84,0:08:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you're working out, the bigger and stronger your hippocampus and prefrontal cortex get.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that important? Because the prefrontal cortex and the hippocampus are the two areas
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.04,0:09:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That are most susceptible to neurodegenerative diseases and normal cognitive decline in aging.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.42,0:09:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So with increased exercise over your lifetime, you're not going to cure dementia or Alzheimer's disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.40,0:09:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you're going to do is you're going to create the strongest, biggest hippocampus and prefrontal cortex.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.46,0:09:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So it takes longer for these diseases to actually have an effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.86,0:09:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You can think of exercise therefore as a supercharged 401k for your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.72,0:09:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's even better because it's free.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.38,0:09:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a point in the talk where everybody says
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.80,0:09:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds so interesting, Wendy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.28,0:09:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But I really only want to know one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.80,0:09:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is just tell me the minimum amount of exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.54,0:09:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to get all these changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.98,0:09:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to tell you the answer to that question. First, good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.84,0:10:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to become a triathlete to get these effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.76,0:10:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The rule of thumb is you want to get three to four times a week exercise
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.02,0:10:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Minimum 30 minutes and exercise session
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.34,0:10:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And you want to get aerobic exercise in that is get your heart rate up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.40,0:10:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the good news is you don't have to go to the gym
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.52,0:10:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To get a very expensive gym membership.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.90,0:10:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Add an extra walk around the block in your power walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.58,0:10:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You see stairs? Take stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.04,0:10:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And power vacuuming can be as good as the aerobics class
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.26,0:10:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That you're going to take at the gym.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.16,0:10:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have gone from memory pioneer to exercise explorer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.82,0:10:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,From going into the innermost workings of the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,To try and understand how exercise can improve our brain function.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.04,0:10:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And my goal in my lab right now is to go beyond that rule of thumb
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.98,0:10:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That I just gave you: three to four times a week, 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.26,0:10:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to understand the optimum exercise prescription for you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.86,0:11:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At your age, at your fitness level,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.24,0:11:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For your genetic background to maximize the effects of exercise today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.44,0:11:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And also to improve your brain and protect your brain the best
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.84,0:11:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For the rest of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.86,0:11:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's one thing to talk about exercise and it's another to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.06,0:11:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to invoke my power as a certified exercise instructor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.40,0:11:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To ask you all to stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.30,0:11:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to do just one minute of exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.64,0:11:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called response.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.84,0:11:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Just do what I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.04,0:11:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Say what I say and make sure you don't punch your neighbor. Okay? Music.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.32,0:11:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,5, 6, 7, 8. It's right left, right left.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.56,0:11:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, I am strong now. Let's hear you. I am strong now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.78,0:11:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies, I am Wonder Woman's Royal, let's hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.98,0:12:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,New move, uppercuts, right and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.46,0:12:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I am inspired now, you say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.02,0:12:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move, pull it down, right and left, right and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.56,0:12:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, I am on fire now, you say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.22,0:12:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I am on fire now. And done, okay? Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.55,0:12:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.77,0:12:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to leave you with one last thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.61,0:12:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is bringing exercise in your life will not only
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.09,0:12:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Give you a happier and more protective life today,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.05,0:12:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But it will protect your brain from insurable diseases
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.15,0:12:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this way it will change the trajectory of your life for the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.01,0:12:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
